ACTIVITY NOTES FOR:

https://edabit.com/challenge/aWzxPLibBLJgn8AbZ

PROMPT:

Write a function that returns true if there exists at least one number in an int[] that is larger than or equal to n.

ELEMENTS:

1) array for loop
2) relational operators

MY THOUGHTS:

My first thought is just to parse the array in a simple for loop and return true as soon as a value that's greater than or equal to the given number.

PROTOTYPE:

public boolean existsHigher(int[] inputArray, int targetNumber){

	if (inputArray.length > 0) {
		for (int i = 0; i < inputArray.length; i++) {
			if (inputArray[i] >= targetNumber) {
				return true;
			} else {
				return false;
			}
		}
	} else {
		return false;
	}
}

